==Jamaican Patois==
===Etymology===
Reportedly derived from [[bum]] [[cloth]], a reference to cloth used in the manner of [[toilet paper]], or from [[blood]] cloth, a reference to cloth used to catch [[menstrual]] blood prior to the invention of [[tampon]]s and similar devices.

===Alternate spellings===
Sometimes spelled with different combinations of vowels, or with a 'k' in place of the 'c' e.g., [[bumboclot]], [[bumbaclat]], [[bumbaklaat]]; sometimes written as two words, e.g., [[bumba clot]].

===Interjection===
'''bumbaclot'''
# {{vulgar}}: To be cheated on.
# {{vulgar}}: General expression of annoyance, disgust, or dismay.


